        <p> {{ page.overview.intro|raw }} to drive seven stations towards Adeje. From there we walked back to the hotel in a relaxed manner. In between we returned to restaurants, strolled through small shops and simply enjoyed the beautiful weather and the warm temperatures. </p>
        <p> Today after breakfast it went straight to the bathing suits and to the beach loungers of our hotel. The hotel has made its own, locked area with poured sand, loungers, parasols, a beach bar and an infinitypool - really great at the bottom of the promenade. Since Basti had to work again at short notice (but there is a meal from the boss as compensation), I was alone in the sun. It burned quite strongly today, so I was all the more happy when Basti finally came and we immediately made our way into the sea together to snorkel. </p>
        <p> The water was pleasantly cool, beautifully clear and shimmered in fantastic shades of blue. Unfortunately, it gets deeply deep after going in, so that you have to swim to the wave breakers in order to be back in a visible zone as a snorkeler. There are a few really large stones on the way there, on which one or the other fish can also be seen, but there was simply more going on on the wave jar - and more beautiful. </p>

